I need to change the layout slightly - I want to use peer checked classes to give the label a ring-digital when focued. Can it be done with the current markup (using child selectors) or is it better to reorganize?
The peer selector needs the input to be a sibling of the elements you want to style, so we'll need to reorganize the markup slightly. Here's how we can modify it:

```tsx
export default function ProductSwitch({
  options,
  testIdPrefix = '',
  name,
}: Props) {
  const theme = useTheme();
  const optionStyles = {
    '--background-color': theme.alias.background_400,
